==Contents==
On this wiki you will find:
* Repository of UnaMesa materials, project coordination, and [[:Category:HowTo|HowTo]] pages for using tools to improve social services
* [[:Category:Story|Stories]] of problems facing schools, clinics, other social service agencies, along with innovative, practical solutions
* Information about the UnaMesa Association itself, including copyrights, contribution agreements, and history

Except as noted, materials on this wiki outside of the ''User:'' pages may be freely used for noncommercial purposes under a creative commons license.  For details see [[Project:Copyrights]] and our [[principles of fairness]]. 

== How you can help ==
* Share your story.  
** Have you found a great way to help teachers or nurses?  [[Share your success story]] so everybody can learn from your experience.  
** Is something making it difficult or impossible for you to serve your constituents? You are not alone.  Try [[asking for help]]. 
* See the [[UnaMesa:Community Portal|community portal]] for details on [[:Category:Help wanted|help wanted]], [[:Category:Help offered|help offered]], and current activities.

== Status of this wiki ==
[http://www.sharedrecords.org SharedRecords.org], [http://www.tiddlywiki.org TiddlyWiki.org], ServiceLink and other UnaMesa projects have been going on for several years.  These projects were originally supported by the Digital Vision program at [http://www.stanford.edu/  Stanford University] and the Community Network Services group at [http://www.rii.ricoh.com/ Ricoh Innovations] until the UnaMesa Assocation was formally established in September 2006.  On June 1, 2007 we established this wiki as the official repository for UnaMesa resources and will be migrating existing materials to this wiki over the next several weeks.

